      "learned": "Chemical bond type determines resultant structure (giant ionic lattice, simple molecular, giant covalent network, metallic lattice), and resultant structure directly determines measurable physical properties (melting point, solubility, electrical conductivity, hardness), which in turn determine the specific everyday uses of each substance in Kenya — from NaCl in ugali cooking to graphite in pencils to aluminium in sufuria to SiO₂ in construction sand along Kenyan riverbeds.",
